# Backend Google Sheets Configuration (SECURE - Server-side only)
# These credentials are now stored securely on the backend

# Your Google Sheets document ID (from the URL)
GOOGLE_SHEETS_ID=your_spreadsheet_id_here

# Google API Key (for read-only access)
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# Google OAuth2 Credentials (for read/write access)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_oauth_client_id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_oauth_client_secret
GOOGLE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_access_token_here
GOOGLE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_refresh_token_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Create a Google Cloud Project
# 2. Enable Google Sheets API
# 3. Create credentials (API Key and OAuth2)
# 4. Copy this file to .env and fill in your values (WITHOUT EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix)
# 5. Make sure your Google Sheet has the following column structure:
#    Column A: item_name
#    Column B: item_code  
#    Column C: stock_vol
#    Column D: unit_measurement
#    Column E: min_value
#    Column F: location
#    Column G: last_updated

# SECURITY NOTE:
# These environment variables are now backend-only and will not be exposed to the client.
# The frontend will communicate with your secure API endpoints instead of directly with Google Sheets.